race.comment: EL TORO MACHO (2) was heavily bet and improved sharply when narrowly beaten at Hawkesbury, and then went to Kembla Grange and got caught wide and raced keenly with the blinkers on for the first time. He arrives here on a 17-day return with Bates booked. In the premiere stable, and this is a winnable assignment. ADAMANA (6) was expected to win here first-up and was never in the hunt (vet cleared). Her second-up Geelong placing three back stacks right up, and the blinkers go on for the first time. Quick improvement is likely. PUMP THE PEDALS (4) has his third start and can improve on the close-up efforts at Bendigo and Moe. She races forward, and Linda rides. Should be right in the finish. BLACK EYED BLONDE (7) has been racing well, and she has pieces of form that would see her very competitive.
